<p>April 1 1918<br/>Easter Monday<br/>Bank Holiday<br/>Left Glasgow and went to Edinburgh. Saw most of what is worth seeing in the Royal Mile &ndash; in the old part of the City In the afternoon Cpl Holm &amp; I went down to the big Forth Bridge which is said to be the greatest bit of steel bridge building in the world. Spent an enjoyable day.</p>
<p>1918 April 2<br/>Tuesday<br/>I had a further look around the city in the morning and went into a kind of Social in the afternoon given to a party from the Club by Mrs Martin a few miles out from Edinburgh. We spent a very pleasant afternoon.</p>
